<p itemprop="description">A senior command and control centre manager leads strategic operational coordination activities and establishes best practices for operational centres. They drive continuous improvement in operational processes and develop organisational operational capabilities.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead strategic development of command and control centre capabilities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish operational procedures and best practices for multiple centres</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop operational management staff</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive automation and efficiency improvements in operational processes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead major incident coordination and post-incident reviews</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with senior leaders on operational strategy and planning</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support business continuity and disaster recovery planning</li>
    </ul>
</section>

